# Project Roadmap

This roadmap outlines the planned features, enhancements, and goals for the Incident Response PowerShell toolkit. It's a living document that reflects our commitment to continuous improvement and community-driven development.

**Last Updated**: December 2024  
**Maintainer**: [@spearsies](https://github.com/spearsies)

---

## üéØ Vision & Mission

### Vision
To provide the most comprehensive, efficient, and user-friendly PowerShell-based DFIR toolkit for security professionals worldwide.

### Mission
- **Empower incident responders** with automated evidence collection
- **Streamline investigations** through standardized data formats
- **Accelerate threat hunting** with pre-built analysis modules
- **Foster collaboration** within the security community
- **Maintain excellence** through continuous improvement

---

## üìä Current Status

### ‚úÖ Completed Features (v2.x)

- [x] Core DFIR artifact collection (25+ artifacts)
- [x] CSV export for SIEM integration
- [x] Microsoft Defender for Endpoint Live Response support
- [x] Modular script architecture (Acquisition/Analysis/Containment)
- [x] Browser history collection (Chrome, Edge, Firefox)
- [x] PowerShell command history extraction
- [x] Network artifact collection
- [x] Process and service enumeration
- [x] Persistence mechanism detection
- [x] Automated evidence packaging (ZIP)
- [x] Comprehensive documentation
- [x] BSD 3-Clause licensing

### üîÑ In Progress

- [ ] Enhanced YARA rule integration
- [ ] Sigma rule detection capabilities
- [ ] Improved error handling and logging
- [ ] Performance optimization for large environments

